SIMPLE: offensive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Offensive
<hw>Of*fen"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>offensif</ets>. See <er>Offend</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Giving offense; causing displeasure or resentment;
displeasing; annoying; <as>as, <ex>offensive</ex> words</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Giving pain or unpleasant sensations; disagreeable;
revolting; noxious; <as>as, an <ex>offensive</ex> smell;
<ex>offensive</ex> sounds.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Offensive</xex> to the
stomach.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Making the first attack; assailant; aggressive;
hence, used in attacking; -- opposed to <ant>defensive</ant>; <as>as, an
<ex>offensive</ex> war; <ex>offensive</ex> weapons.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>League offensive and defensive</b></col>, <cd>a leaque
that requires all the parties to it to make war together against any
foe, and to defend one another if attacked.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Displeasing; disagreeable; distasteful;
obnoxious; abhorrent; disgusting; impertinent; rude; saucy; reproachful;
opprobrious; insulting; insolent; abusive; scurrilous; assailant;
attacking; invading.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Of*fen"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Of*fen"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Offensive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Offensive
<hw>Of*fen"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or
posture of one who offends or makes attack; aggressive attitude; the act
of the attacking party; -- opposed to <ant>defensive</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>To take the offensive</b></col>, <col><b>To act on
the offensive</b></col>, <col><b>To go on the
offensive</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to be the attacking party; to initiate
hostilities.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Offer</ent>⟦br⟧
